      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. they made it to the final round for a senior dev role here in austin but we decided to go with someone else. they were actually really good and had great technical skills, so i want the email to be professional and kind but still clear that we aren't moving forward. can u help me draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here are a few options, but I'll give you a template that balances professionalism with kindness. You want to be clear, but you also want to leave the door open for future opportunities. It's important to be gracious, even when the decision is tough.\n\nHere is a draft:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview for the Senior Developer role and for sharing your impressive technical skills with our team. We truly enjoyed getting to know you throughout the final round interviews. While your background is incredibly strong, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose specific experience more closely aligned with the immediate needs of this particular role. We wish you the very best in your job search and future endeavors.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\"\n\n***\n\n*Self-Correction/Refinement:* You might want to add a sentence about keeping them in mind for future roles, which softens the blow even more.\n\nHere is a slightly warmer alternative:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you again for investing your time in the interview process for the Senior Developer position. Your technical acumen and insights during the final round were genuinely impressive, and we were very impressed with your capabilities.",
